               <msContents>
                  <summary>Images 2l-xxx: Harp of Praise, Arganonä Wǝddase, አርጋኖነ፡ ውዳሴ፡, arranged for the days of the week. Pontus Leander, `Arganona Ueddase nach Handschriften in Uppsala, Berlin, Tübingen und Frankfurt a. M. Göteborgs Högskolas Årsskrift 28.3 (Leipzig 1922). Monday (probably covered by illumination), Tuesday (30l), Wednesday (55r), Thursday (70l), Friday (88l and r), Saturday (109r), Sunday (120l). Illuminations added recently over text. Image 69r has the text: ተፈጸመ በዝየ መንፈቁ ለአርጋኖን ውዳሴሃ. . . Image 70l, top margin, contains the name of a secondary owner, ክብረ ሚካኤል. Image 130l mentions the original owner, መንግስተ አብ, and his daughter, ወለተ ድንግል, and a secondary owner ኃበነ ሚካኤል.</summary>
